{"word":"ἑδριάω","slug":"ἑδριάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑδριάω</b></el> <el>(ἑδριάω,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to seat</i> or <i>set</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to sit</i>, in epic forms 3rd <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>ἑδριόωνται, ἑδριόωντο</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>ἑδριάασθαι</el>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <i>to sit</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}